    <title>Remove field from document type</title>
  </properties>

  <body>
    <section name="Remove field from document type">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to remove a field from a document type?</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=450;
    toppx=250;
    bottompx=600;
   </script>
   <div class='group'>
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M9/inars/remove_field_from_documenttype.png" alt='remove field screenshot'/> 
    </div></div>
    <p>
      In a document type, fields can be removed by clicking on their remove button.
    </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    Ensure that you have the document type in <a href='../concepts/edit_mode.html'>edit mode</a>.
    Click on the remove button at the upper right of a field to remove it.
   </p>
   <div class='alert-48 icon-text-48'>
     If you remove a field from a document type, while documents of that type
     already exists, all information in that field from all those documents will be lost!
   </div>

   <p>The changes will be available only after <a href='./update_all_content.html'>update all content</a>.
      Read the warnings about it carefully. You may add or change more fields first.
   </p>

